==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quivered
<hw>Quiv"ered</hw> <pr>(kw⟦icr⟧v"⟦etil⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Furnished with, or carrying, a quiver.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Like a <xex>quivered</xex> nymph with arrows keen.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sheathed, as in a quiver.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Whose quills
stand <xex>quivered</xex> at his ear.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quiveringly</ent>⟦br⟧
